<body>
<div id="country3" class="tabcontent">
<div style="width: 740px; border: 1px dashed gray; padding: 10px;  margin:0px auto;">
<h2>IPD Nursing Entry</h2>
<hr />
<span class="title">Screen Overview </span><br />
This screen captures the details of all patient nursing care entry details.
<br /><hr /><br />
<img src="images/IPD_nursingentry.jpg" width="725"  /><br /><br />
<hr />
<p>

<span class="title">Select Care:</span> <br />
On clicking of nursing entry button user can access nursing entry screen.
User can select the nursing care from the given list, this will come from nursing care setup screen, it can't remain blank.

<br />
  <span class="title">Date:</span> 
    <br />Default system date and present date will display, User canâ€™t change the date.
<br />
    <span class="title">Time of care (HH:MM):</span> 
    <br />Default system and present time will display, User can modify the time.
<br />
    <span class="title">Care details:</span> 
    <br />Based on user selection of patient care all patient details will display based care setup and date. 
<br />
    <span class="title">GRID (Display): </span> 
    <br />Based on patient care data will display in the form of table. At a time only ten records will be displayed. To navigate or look for the next record pagination (the system of numbering pages) will be there. 
<br />
    <span class="title">OK Button and Text Box: </span> 
    <br />If user wants to switch directly to any particular page no., the he can simply enter the page no. in the given text box and click on Go Button
    
    <br />
    <span class="title">Patient details:</span> 
    <br />Based on care setup all patients details will display against selected care.
          User can select any patient and user can click count of care for particular day.
          User can write remarks against patient.
          
    <br />
    <span class="title">Submit (Button):</span> 
    <br />By clicking on Submit button user can save the data. 
          
     <br />
    <span class="title">Back (Button):</span> 
    <br />Clicking on Back button, will move user to the previous screen.


       
</p>
</div>
